1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,400
What happens when one predator disappears?

2
00:00:02,400 --> 00:00:07,600
Meet the mesopredator—smaller predators like foxes and raccoons—who thrive when larger predators vanish.

3
00:00:07,600 --> 00:00:12,400
This shift can lead to overpopulation, impacting local ecosystems in unexpected ways.

4
00:00:12,400 --> 00:00:18,000
Studies indicate that mesopredator release alters prey dynamics, causing a ripple effect on biodiversity.

5
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:20,800
But here’s the catch—effects can vary widely.

6
00:00:20,800 --> 00:00:23,600
Not all ecosystems respond the same way.

7
00:00:23,600 --> 00:00:27,200
Want to dive deeper into the complexities of ecosystems?

